snippet: Gen. Abdul-Fattah el-Sisi is riding a wave of muscular nationalism and pro-military sentiment, leaving questions of how quickly he intends to return the country to civilian rule.
abstract: Egyptian military leader Gen Abdul-Fattah el-Sisi is riding a wave of muscular nationalism and pro-military sentiment after deposing Pres Mohammed Morsi, leaving questions of how quickly he intends to return Egypt to civilian rule.

byline.contributor: Mayy El Sheikh contributed reporting from Cairo.

lead_paragraph: Gen. Abdul-Fattah el-Sisi is riding a wave of muscular nationalism and pro-military sentiment, leaving questions of how quickly he intends to return the country to civilian rule.
